---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Custom Integrations — DH7" description="Custom software integrations for small businesses. Connect your systems so data flows where it needs to, automatically.">

  <div class="max-w-lg">
    <h1 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] text-3xl font-600 tracking-tight text-[#2A2520] mb-6">🔌 Integrations</h1>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#2A2520]">
      Most small businesses run on a handful of software tools that don't talk to each other. Data lives in separate places. People move it between systems by hand. Things get missed. Things go wrong.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
      Custom integrations fix that by connecting your systems so data flows where it needs to, automatically.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-16 space-y-12">

    <div class="border-t border-[#E6DFD0] pt-10">
      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] font-600 text-lg text-[#2A2520] mb-3">What I build</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-[#2A2520]">Point-to-point integrations between the tools you already use — CRMs, accounting packages, booking systems, inventory tools, communication platforms. Whatever the combination, I can connect them.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-[#E6DFD0] pt-10">
      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] font-600 text-lg text-[#2A2520] mb-3">Why custom?</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-[#2A2520]">Off-the-shelf integration tools handle simple cases. For anything more specific — your data model, your workflow, your edge cases — you need something built to fit.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-[#2A2520]">Custom integrations are built around your actual workflow, not a generic template. You own the code, not a SaaS subscription. There's no third-party middleware that can go down or change its pricing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-[#E6DFD0] pt-10">
      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] font-600 text-lg text-[#2A2520] mb-3">Who this is for</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-[#2A2520]">Small businesses that have outgrown manual processes. If you're copying and pasting data between systems, re-entering information, or spending time on reconciliation — that's time and money you don't need to spend.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-[#E6DFD0] pt-10">
      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] font-600 text-lg text-[#2A2520] mb-4">Examples of the systems I work with</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2">
        {[
          { href: '/integrations/current-rms', label: 'Current RMS', desc: 'Rental and events management' },
          { href: '/integrations/pipedrive', label: 'Pipedrive', desc: 'CRM and sales pipeline' },
          { href: '/integrations/maxoptra', label: 'Maxoptra', desc: 'Route planning and delivery' },
          { href: '/integrations/deputy', label: 'Deputy', desc: 'Workforce management and scheduling' },
          { href: '/integrations/samsara', label: 'Samsara', desc: 'Fleet management and telematics' },
        ].map(({ href, label, desc }) => (
          <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
            <a href={href} class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] font-500 text-[#A87820] hover:underline no-underline">{label}</a>
            <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] text-sm text-[#7A7068]">{desc}</span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-[#E6DFD0] pt-10">
      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] font-600 text-lg text-[#2A2520] mb-3">✉️ Contact</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-[#2A2520]">Tell me what systems you're running and where the friction is. I'll tell you what's possible.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] inline-block mt-4 text-[#A87820] hover:underline no-underline">✉️ Contact →</a>
    </div>

  </div>

</Base>
